E

E - Class in edu.frontrange.csc240.a3
Prints an estimate of the value of the constant e by evaluating the series expansion to a number of terms given by the user.
E() - Constructor for class edu.frontrange.csc240.a3.E
 
e_estimate(int) - Method in class edu.frontrange.csc240.a3.E
Compute the value of e_estimate, the base of natural logarithms, using the Taylor expansion, as accurately as possible to the given number of terms, which is assumed (precondition) to be greater than or equal to 1.
edu.frontrange.csc240.a3 - package edu.frontrange.csc240.a3
 
edu.frontrange.csc240.util - package edu.frontrange.csc240.util
 
Ex - Class in edu.frontrange.csc240.a3
Prints the value of the e to x expansion to a number of terms input by the user, and an exponent input by the user.
Ex() - Constructor for class edu.frontrange.csc240.a3.Ex
 
exponential(double, int) - Method in class edu.frontrange.csc240.a3.Ex
Compute the value of e, the base of natural logarithms, raised to the given exponent, using the Taylor expansion, as accurately as possible with the given number of terms, which is assumed to be greater than or equal to 1.
